Hi @ceb21!

I'm not quite sure what you're trying to do, but you can bind to the [`sortBegin` event](https://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/#sortbegin) and modify the [`sortList`](https://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/#sortlist). It doesn't include any parameters like your `onSort` example, but you can access the processed `sortList` before modifying it - [demo](https://jsfiddle.net/Mottie/bbxxomhx/402/):

```js
$(function() {
  $('table')
  .on('sortBegin', function(event, table) {
    // use this or table
  	this.config.sortList = [[0,0]];
  })
  .tablesorter({
    theme: 'blue',
    sortList: [[0, 1], [2, 1]],
    sortMultiSortKey: "ctrlKey"
  });
});
```

I'm not sure what kind of grouping you have set up, but have you checked out the [group widget](https://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/example-widget-grouping.html)? Also, you might find the [`sortAppend` option](https://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/#sortappend) useful, or even interesting.

