Anywhere a user is catching `BotocoreError` they would suddenly be catching a whole new class of errors. Anywhere a user is only catching a `ClientError` there would be no issue. Anywhere a user is catching both and performing different actions there may be a breaking change depending on the ordering of the catches. Something like the following would break:

```python
try:
    client.service_call()
except BotocoreError:
    # panic
except ClientError:
    # show error to user
```

