@mcg1969 Added some comments/questions to https://github.com/conda/conda/pull/2853.  In general, I think we need an opt-in* flag to revert behavior exactly back to 4.0.x behavior and expectations.  People need to be able to revert exactly to the old behavior until they catch their CI systems and such up.  At some point we could deprecate the option, but we should provide some transition period.

Basically, as @janschulz says, if it's not the `channel_priority` flag that drops `channel_priority` out of the calculation entirely, then we should add another option that does.

\* Opt-in because (1) the cat is out of the bag on 4.1.x, and (2) I'm fine pushing/forcing users toward better practices once we improve our processes (e.g. forthcoming announcement list, forthcoming canary program, etc.).

