A simple solution to work around this problem is to modify the `url` function of `ImageFile` so that it composes the _MEDIA URL_ using the standard storage (or a simple function such as `urljoin(base_url, url)`) instead of the DFS API. 

The reason behind this is to overcome the lag _(0.5-1.5s)_ introduced by the DFS API (here _django-storages_ -> _Apache LibCloud - Google Cloud_) when asking for URL directly to the DFS.


In _sorl/thumbnail/images.py:_

```
from django.core.files.storage import FileSystemStorage


class ImageFile(BaseImageFile):
     [...]

     def __init__(self, file_, storage=None):
          # Add this line
          self.standard_storage = FileSystemStorage()

     [...]

     @property
         def url(self):
             if settings.THUMBNAIL_FAST_URL:
                 return self.standard_storage.url(self.name)
             else:
                 return self.storage.url(self.name)
```

`THUMBNAIL_FAST_URL` is a boolean variable set in _settings.py_ to enable this function.

